I feel like I have been taking this survey forever (haha). Anyways it is interesting to reflect on my friendship with the candidate now and what our friendship was like when we first met. I think we have both grown a lot over the past 3-4 years, however I would say that the core of our respective personalities have remained the same. Interestingly enough although we ended up taking very different academic paths (we both started with similar majors and our friendship kinda started as study buddies, now we are in different schools) we have stayed in touch. I also feel like we have become more like each other over the years (bizarre I know). Anyways I will miss her when we graduate in 
May :( . I will miss a lot of people, but I will probably miss her the most. 

Also will you email the results (to me or other participants) of these surveys to the participants when it is done? One thing I have noticed as a participant in a multitude of studies over the years is that I never learn of the results/conclusion of the study even though I may have been a part of said study for years. Its like the researchers use us for data (about myself and my peers) and then don't bother to share it with the people they were studying when its done. I too would like to learn about the personality and self-knowledge of myself and my peers. Anyways, that's my two cents.
